      "Additional water applied to extinguish residual hot spots",
      "100kw generator recovery scheduled for mid-February"
    ],
    "summary": "On 26-Nov-2015 at approximately 1030 hours, a fire was observed on the unmanned, shut-in Padre North 975 A platform during an overflight. The fire occurred on the top wooden deck in the Northeast corner. Hot work construction had concluded approximately 42 hours prior on 24-Nov-2015. Two operators were transported to the platform and successfully extinguished the fire using water from the MV Hercules by 2030 hours. All hot spots were extinguished by 2300 hours. Approximately 2/3 of the top wooden deck was consumed. A 100kw generator was presumed lost overboard. Total property damage estimated at $95,000. No injuries or pollution events reported.",
